{{Quote|The specific tenets of the Jedi Order, however, are believed to have been set down on the dawn world of Tython where many Force-users harnessed a positive energy called the Ashla. Those who hungered to wield the Force for personal power dragged the planet into an exhausting conflict known as the Force Wars. From the ashes of this conflict, the Force users of Tython established the Jedi as a society of monastic warriors who obeyed the precepts of harmony, knowledge, serenity, and peace.|[[Historical Council]] of the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]]|<ref name="NEC" />}}
The '''Force Wars''' were a ten year long series of conflicts that took place on [[Tython/Legends|Tython]] more than seven centuries before the formation of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. They were considered the first conflicts between the followers of the [[Light side of the Force/Legends|light]] and [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark]] sides of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. The Force Wars originally began as an [[Invasion of the Tython system|invasion by the forces of the]] [[Rakata/Legends|Rakatan]] [[Infinite Empire/Legends|Infinite Empire]].

==History==
===Prelude===
The Force Wars of Tython have their origins in the years following the [[Despot War]] which pitted the armies of [[Hadiya]], a queen of [[Shikaakwa]], against the [[Je'daii Order]]. Around [[25,800 BBY]], [[Je'daii Master]] [[Daegen Lok]] deviated from the conventional wisdom and descended into the [[Chasm]] below [[Anil Kesh]] temple, where he and his companion [[Hawk Ryo]] were overcome by a terrible [[Force vision/Legends|Force vision]]<ref name="DOTJ 6">[[Dawn of the Jedi: The Prisoner of Bogan 1|''Dawn of the Jedi: The Prisoner of Bogan'' 1]]</ref> Within their vision, an army of dark warriors wielding [[Forcesaber|blades of frozen fire]] marching across [[Ska Gora]],<ref name="DOTJ 7">[[Dawn of the Jedi: The Prisoner of Bogan 2|''Dawn of the Jedi: The Prisoner of Bogan'' 2]]</ref> led by a [[Tau (individual)|being with one red eye]].<ref name="DOTJ 6" /> To combat this, they saw themselves leading the Je'daii armies against the threat.<ref name="DOTJ 10">[[Dawn of the Jedi: The Prisoner of Bogan 5|''Dawn of the Jedi: The Prisoner of Bogan'' 5]]</ref> Driven mad by the visions, Lok fell to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]], and was taken before the [[Je'daii Council]] for questioning. Despite his passion, the Council did not believe in Lok's vision or warning and banished him to the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] of [[Bogan]] until he renounced his vision and returned to Balance in the Force. Over the next seven years, Lok lived out his exile in solitude, carving an enormous mural of himself wielding the blade of fire, and numerous pictures of the weapon.<ref name="DOTJ 6" />

===War with the Infinite Empire===
{{Main|Invasion of the Tython system}}
===War of light and darkness===
{{Quote|The stories said that a great war ensued between the two groups, with the worshipers of Ashla emerging victorious.|Legends recalled by [[Darth Bane/Legends|Darth Bane]]|<ref name="ROT">''[[Darth Bane: Rule of Two]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Force_wars_JMGD.jpg|left|300px]]
While the Rakatan threat was defeated,<ref name="DOTJ 15">[[Dawn of the Jedi: Force War 5|''Dawn of the Jedi: Force War'' 5]]</ref> the Je'daii split into two groups, one which used the [[Light side of the Force/Legends|Ashla]], which would later be called the light side of the Force to achieve knowledge, and another which used the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|Bogan]], which would later be called the dark side of the Force to gain power. Both sides utilized the traditional [[Force-imbued sword/Legends|metal swords augmented]] through [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. When the Ashla Je'daii established the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]]<ref name="NEC" /> under the leadership of a [[Jedi High Council/Legends|High Council]], peace seemed imminent until the [[Rajivari's purges|defection]] of revered Master [[Rajivari]]. Holing up within [[Kaleth]], [[Rajivari's followers]] fought to the death, and were subsequently defeated.<ref name="TOR">''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]''</ref>

===Conclusion===
In [[25,783 BBY]], a [[Force Cataclysm|cataclysm]] destroyed the planet's biosphere, rendering the world uninhabitable.<ref name="TORencyclopedia" /> What Ashla Je'daii survived fled to the [[Rim]] before settling on [[Ossus/Legends|Ossus]].<ref name="Atlas">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>

While the young [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] banned travel to Tython, the Jedi Order occasionally returned briefly, though they would not resettle their homeworld until the [[Cold War (Galactic Republic–Sith Empire)|Cold War]], after [[Satele Shan]] rediscovered the planet, shortly after the [[Treaty of Coruscant]]. Rumors existed during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] that a secret temple existed on the world where they kept their hidden treasures.<ref name="NoP">''[[Nexus of Power]]''</ref>

{{Noncanonstart|legends=1}}
The Force Wars were studied by [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] students at the [[Jedi academy]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] as part of Mrs. [[Pilton]]'s course on the History of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]]. [[Roan Novachez]] was weak in his knowledge of this subject-- on his report card for the course in the third semester, he earned a B+ with a note that his studies were "excellent, except for study of major events during the Force Wars."<ref name="Academy">''[[Jedi Academy: Return of the Padawan]]''</ref>
{{Noncanonend}}

